snippet.textDisplay: I see the serial negativists on the comments already. This is a gamechanging feature I think. It's probably configured to be a button push, it's probably using torquevectoring technology. It's probably programmed to take it easy on the torque if slip levels are low to save tire wear. Of course it will wear a little bit on asphalt, but it won't be catastrophic. It will be awesome in parking garages and tight driveways as well as high congestion events. It's a gamechanger also in offroading. I don't see a negative to this car having this feature. The only negative in these next generation electric cars is the battery technology and the range, although the latter is almost as good as fuel cars now. Everything else is better.
